OL,6,F(HSE) inspector Rhys Hughes said
OL,7,FAtlantic Recycling failed to ensure
OL,8,Fpedestrians and vehicles were
OL,9,Fseparated at its site.
OL,11,FThe investigation also found that
OL,12,Falthough a risk assessment had been
OL,13,Fproduced prior to the work commencing,
OL,14,Fit was not suitable nor sufficient and
OL,15,Fdid not include work taking place in
OL,16,Fthe wood yard.
OL,18,FIt also said the assessment should
OL,19,Fhave identified there was a risk to
OL,20,Fpedestrians where there were moving
OL,21,Fvehicles.
